Generate polyA vs stranded plots on known samples: PT_RYMG3M91 and PT_W5GP3F6B

We would like to assess the correlation between PSI values generated with polyA vs stranded samples. First, samples from PT_RYMG3M91 - very tight correlation.

# General plots assessing PSI in poly A vs Str for known samples PT_RYMG3M91 and PT_W5GP3F6B
clin_to_check_df <- clin_df %>% 
  filter(Kids_First_Participant_ID %in% c('PT_RYMG3M91', 'PT_W5GP3F6B'))

# Select two sample_ids for comparison
polya_id <- "BS_68KX6A42"
stranded_id <- "BS_D7XRFE0R"

# Filter data for selected sample IDs
psi_PT_RYMG3M91 <- rmats_df %>% 
  filter(sample_id %in% c(polya_id, stranded_id)) %>% 
  filter(splicing_case=='SE') %>%
  dplyr::mutate(SpliceID = paste(geneSymbol, exonStart_0base, exonEnd, upstreamES,upstreamEE,downstreamES,downstreamEE, sep = ":")) %>%
  dplyr::select(sample_id,SpliceID,IncLevel1)

# Filter data for the selected sample_ids
sample1_data <- psi_PT_RYMG3M91 %>%
  filter(sample_id == polya_id)
sample2_data <- psi_PT_RYMG3M91 %>%
  filter(sample_id == stranded_id)

# Merge data for the same SpliceID
merged_data <- merge(sample1_data, sample2_data, by = "SpliceID", suffixes = c("_polya", "_stranded"))

# Create scatterplot using ggscatter
library(ggplot2)

# Scatter plot with outlined circles
PT_RYMG3M91_scatter <- ggplot(merged_data, aes(x = IncLevel1_polya, y = IncLevel1_stranded)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = "black"), shape = 21, size = 2, fill = NA) + # Outlined circles
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", aes(color = "red"), se = TRUE) + # Regression line with confidence interval in red
  labs(x = paste(polya_id, "PSI (poly-A)"), y = paste(stranded_id, "PSI (stranded)")) +
  theme_Publication() + # Use a minimal theme; replace with theme_Publication() if you have it
  scale_color_identity() # To ensure colors specified in aes() are used directly

# Print the plot
print(PT_RYMG3M91_scatter)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# Save
pdf(PT_RYMG3M91_scatter_path, height = 4, width = 4, useDingbats = FALSE)
print(PT_RYMG3M91_scatter)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
dev.off()
## png

Investigating the edge cases with low correlation

So I did some investigating, and the 0 PSI cases essentially are splice events that have 0 inclusion junction counts. So, when PSI is calculated its IJC/(IJC+SJC). SJC are skip junction counts. These is rare cases, but below I show an example for ABAT.

This would mean that exon skipping is occurring 100% of the time. There are few cases where its 0 in one and >70% in another condition. For those cases, its likely they are very low expressed genes or non-coding.

rmats_df %>% 
  filter(sample_id=='BS_68KX6A42', geneSymbol=='ABAT') %>% 
  dplyr::select(IJC_SAMPLE_1,SJC_SAMPLE_1, exonStart_0base, exonEnd)
